# NextBSD in-kernel IORegistry (K1, nextbsd#214) — appended to sys/conf/files by
# the kernel build. Source under sys/dev/iokit, laid in from the nextbsd-kernel
# src-overlay. `standard`: always compiled into the kernel (read-only newbus
# introspection; inert until queried via /dev/ioregistry or hw.iokit.registry).
# Wired in build.yml, NOT in patches/series, so the modules build (which shares
# the series but does not lay in the overlay) never sees an absent source — the
# same reasoning as files.iocatalogue.
dev/iokit/iokit_registry.c	standard
